      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Does not interrupt current speech. The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "kNoSpeechInterrupt",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " flagbit is used to control the behavior of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakBuffer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " whencalled on a speech channel that is still busy. When the flag bitis not set, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakBuffer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " behavessimilarly to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakString",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakText",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".Any speech currently being produced on the specified speech channelis immediately interrupted, and then the new text buffer is spoken.When the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "kNoSpeechInterrupt",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " flagbit is set, however, a request to speak on a channel that is stillbusy processing a prior text buffer will result in an error. Thenew buffer is ignored and the error ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "synthNotReady",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " isreturned. If the prior text buffer has been fully processed, thenew buffer is spoken normally. One way of achieving continuous speech without using callback functions is to continually call ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpeakBuffer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "kNoSpeechInterrupt",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " flagbit set until the function returns ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "noErr",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".The function will then execute as soon as the first text bufferhas been processed.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
